Subject: Louka (Blansko District) 
To: Teresa
Content:
Louka is a village and municipality (obec) in Blansko District in the South Moravian Region of the Czech Republic. The municipality covers an area of 8.6 square kilometres (3.3sqmi), and has a population of 69 (as at 28August 2006). Louka lies approximately 24 kilometres (15mi) north-west of Blansko, 38km (24mi) north of Brno, and 158km (98mi) south-east of Prague.
